  "instructions": [
    "Heat a non-stick skillet over medium heat. Add olive oil and cook garlic, onion, and red bell pepper until softened.",
    "Add smoked salmon fillets to the skillet and let them sit for about 2 minutes on each side, allowing the salmon to slightly crisp up.",
    "In a separate bowl, mix together chicken broth and cornstarch until smooth. Gradually pour into the skillet while stirring continuously.",
    "Cook over medium heat until thickened, about 5-7 minutes. Stir in avocado, cilantro, and season with salt and pepper according to taste.",
    "Serve hot as a side dish or main course."
